    <description type="1">
      <narrative xml:lang="en">A USTDA grant to OnePower Lesotho (Proprietary) Limited ("OnePower") will fund a feasibility study and technological design work ("Study") for the development of a 20-megawatt solar power plant near Mafeteng, Lesotho. The project is anticipated to be the first solar independent power production project in Lesotho. Arup USA, Inc. is completing the Study which will support OnePower to address critical technical, financial and legal requirements to implement the power plant. A USTDA grant of $600,000 to OnePower Lesotho (Proprietary) Limited ("OnePower") is supporting a feasibility study to evaluate the viability of a single solar photovoltaic ("PV") inverter block as part of the larger 20-megawatt Neo I Solar PV plant and a local electrification plan in the Ts'ana Talana council of Mafeteng District. The project is anticipated to be the first solar independent power production project in Lesotho. The U.S. firm CDM International, Inc. is completing the study, which will support One Power to address critical technical, financial and legal requirements to implement the power plant.</narrative>
    </description>
